#31303
slumbering creature tupilaq~
a tupilaq~
A slumbering creature fabricated of dark arts creaks and snaps as it moves about searching.
~
This creature has no discernible shape and can only be described as a
terrifying mass of hair, sinew, teeth, and bone.  It seems to be sewn together
with the sinew of different slain animals.  Its eyes are glowing a dark green
and are set deeply into the front of its borrowed skull.  The skull is wrapped tighty in the
stomach lining of some animal and glistens with moisture.  It is sewn onto a
mass of hair belonging to some dark furred animal.  The creature has a jaw that
spans nearly the entire front of its body and articulates open with a set of
fabricated jaws and teeth that could shred diamonds.  Its four limbs are
attached at the body in four asymmetrical points, some with hooves, others
with paws.  The clicking and snapping sound it makes as it travels across the
ground are likely caused by the mismatched joints that have been rigged by its
creator.  
~
